Team - Hood River Capital Management


























































 
 








Investment Team


The interaction of our structure and team drives our outcomes. Hood River Capital Management is 100% owned by the investment team, with our three equal partners acting as co-portfolio managers. All portfolio managers perform their own active research in a generalist role, and each of the three portfolio managers has more than 20 years of experience analyzing small capitalization stocks. Our small cap growth strategy has a strong continuous track record dating back to 2002.



Brian Smoluch, CFA
Principal – Portfolio Manager/Analyst
Investment Experience: 20 Years
Brian founded Hood River Capital Management, which spun out of Roxbury Capital Management, where he managed the Small-Cap Growth product for 10 years.  Prior to Roxbury, Brian was part of the small/mid-cap team at Columbia Management. He began his career as an investment banking financial analyst at Salomon Brothers in New York.
University of Virginia, B.S. with Distinction
Harvard Business School, M.B.A.



David Swank, CFA
Principal – Portfolio Manager/Analyst
Investment Experience: 20 Years
David founded Hood River Capital Management, which spun out of Roxbury Capital Management, where he managed the Small-Cap Growth product for 5 years. Prior to Roxbury, David worked for GMT Capital Corporation as the healthcare sector head of a $4 billion long/short equity hedge fund. He previously worked at Morgan Stanley Investment Management and began his career as a research associate at Furman Selz and Montgomery Securities.
University of Virginia, B.S. with Distinction
The Amos Tuck School at Dartmouth College, M.B.A.



Robert Marvin, CFA
Principal – Portfolio Manager/Analyst
Investment Experience: 24 Years
Rob founded Hood River Capital Management, which spun out of Roxbury Capital Management, where he managed the Small-Cap Growth product for 10 years. Prior to Roxbury, Rob was part of the small/mid-cap team at Columbia Management. Before that Rob was vice president and consumer analyst for the Seidler Companies, a boutique research and brokerage firm. He began his career as a senior consultant at Deloitte & Touche.
University of California at Berkeley, B.S. cum laude – Business Administration
The Anderson School of Business at UCLA, M.B.A.




ROHAN B. KUMAR
Research Analyst
Investment Experience: 6 Years
Rohan joined Hood River in 2015 as a research analyst and has 6 years of investment experience.  Prior to joining Hood River, Rohan was a research analyst at Hawkeye Capital Management.  He previously was an analyst at Reliance Capital and began his career as a Component Design Engineer at Intel.
Rohan has a Bachelor of Technology in electrical engineering from the Indian Institute of Technology at Kharagpur, a Masters from Harvard’s Kennedy School and his M.B.A. from The Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania.




BRET D. HOKKANEN
Director of Sales
Bret joined Hood River in March 2016, and is responsible for sales and client service. Prior to joining Hood River, Bret had the same responsibilities at Tygh Capital Management, a Portland-based money management firm that specializes in small cap and small-mid cap growth investing for institutions and mutual funds. He previously was at Columbia Management with similar duties across many asset classes.
Bret has a B.S. in business from Oregon State University and an M.B.A. from the University of Portland.




MAUREEN L. FLAHERTY
Office Manager/Compliance Designee
Maureen joined Hood River Capital Management in 2013 after working at Roxbury Capital Management for 3 years as the office manager/compliance designee. Before joining Roxbury Capital Management, Maureen worked for SunTrust Mortgage for 5 years as Broker Relations. She also worked on the buy side for 9 years as product manager at Black and Company which later became Wells Fargo Securities.
After transferring from Oregon State University where she studied political science, Maureen received her B.A. in interdisciplinary studies/social science from Marylhurst University.


  







By clicking “Proceed to Commentary Page,” you are acknowledging that you are viewing commentary for the Small Cap Growth separately managed account for our investment advisory services and not our mutual fund.
