Hood River Capital Management LLC Stake in Mastec INC (MTZ) Has Boosted by $10.34 Million


					

						July 26, 2017 - By Darrin Black

Investors sentiment increased to 1.12 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.02, from 1.1 in 2016Q3. It improved, as 20 investors sold MTZ shares while 85 reduced holdings. 62 funds opened positions while 56 raised stakes. 56.54 million shares or 0.99% more from 55.98 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Barclays Public Ltd Co owns 1,004 shares. Principal Financial stated it has 0.03% in MasTec, Inc. (NYSE:MTZ). Driehaus Cap Management Ltd Com accumulated 31,516 shares or 0.04% of the stock. Connecticut-based Point72 Asset Mgmt Lp has invested 0.02% in MasTec, Inc. (NYSE:MTZ). Moreover, Hood River Capital Mngmt Ltd Limited Liability Company has 3.84% invested in MasTec, Inc. (NYSE:MTZ). Fortaleza Asset Mngmt accumulated 0.3% or 3,720 shares. Prudential owns 110,357 shares. California Employees Retirement System reported 0.01% of its portfolio in MasTec, Inc. (NYSE:MTZ). Citadel Advsr Limited Liability Com reported 152,051 shares. Wellington Gp Llp reported 158,266 shares. Stifel Finance owns 7,537 shares. Bessemer Inc accumulated 265 shares. Renaissance Tech Ltd Llc reported 0% stake. State Street Corporation has 1.20M shares. Kbc Gp Nv has 14,574 shares.
Since June 9, 2017, it had 0 insider buys, and 1 sale for $108,939 activity. 






Hood River Capital Management Llc increased its stake in Mastec Inc (MTZ) by 30.88% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Hood River Capital Management Llc bought 272,187 shares as the company’s stock rose 9.66% with the market. The institutional investor held 1.15 million shares of the basic industries company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $44.12 million, up from 881,333 at the end of the previous reported quarter. Hood River Capital Management Llc who had been investing in Mastec Inc for a number of months, seems to be bullish on the $3.77B market cap company. The stock declined 0.54% or $0.25 reaching $46.1 on the news. About 152,604 shares traded. MasTec, Inc. (NYSE:MTZ) has risen 93.42% since July 26, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 76.72% the S&P500.
Hood River Capital Management Llc, which manages about $698.72 million and $1.15B US Long portfolio, decreased its stake in James River Group Holdings L (NASDAQ:JRVR) by 144,982 shares to 247,379 shares, valued at $10.28M in 2016Q4, according to the filing. It also reduced its holding in Pra Health Sciences Inc by 85,752 shares in the quarter, leaving it with 615,451 shares, and cut its stake in Lumentum Holdings Inc. 
Another recent and important MasTec, Inc. (NYSE:MTZ) news was published by Marketwatch.com which published an article titled: “MasTec chairman reportedly buying Miami Marlins for $1.17 billion” on July 10, 2017.
MasTec, Inc. (NYSE:MTZ) Ratings Coverage
Among 11 analysts covering MasTec (NYSE:MTZ), 9 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 2 Hold. Therefore 82% are positive. MasTec had 19 analyst reports since August 3, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The rating was initiated by Robert W. Baird with “Outperform” on Tuesday, August 25. The rating was upgraded by Credit Suisse to “Outperform” on Monday, July 24. The firm has “Neutral” rating given on Wednesday, November 16 by DA Davidson. FBR Capital maintained it with “Outperform” rating and $57 target in Monday, May 8 report. The rating was downgraded by Avondale to “Market Perform” on Friday, November 18. The company was downgraded on Tuesday, August 4 by Zacks. The stock has “Buy” rating by Stephens on Monday, September 21. The company was maintained on Friday, May 26 by Canaccord Genuity. Craig Hallum initiated the shares of MTZ in report on Thursday, November 12 with “Buy” rating. Credit Suisse initiated the shares of MTZ in report on Monday, April 3 with “Neutral” rating.


